A Peking Opera actor prepares for a performance Photo: Courtesy of Ta SuAs part of its 10th anniversary celebrations, the Beijing Performance & Arts Group released the lineup for its annual May Performance Season on Thursday. A total of 20 stage works from various theaters within the group will be staged at 12 venues across the city. Among these events are puppet show Puppet King Returns by the China Puppet Art Theatre, Quju Opera Lin Zexu in Beijing by the Beijing Quju Theater, and Dragon Gate staged by the China Acrobatic Group. At the event, nine theaters staged performances, including a new song Where My Heart Belongs sung by A Yunga and composed by Liao Yong. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Actress Liu honored with Hollywood Walk of Fame starDelegation of HUST attends alumni gala in Los AngelesChinese driving Vegas growth